### Former State of the Holy Roman Empire and part of the Habsburg Netherlands (1091–1795)

This meticulously detailed account concerns the historical entity known as the County of Holland, a political and geographical construct that ceased to exist in its former capacity in 1795. For those with a penchant for geographical overlaps and historical parallels, a distinct administrative county bearing the name [Parts of Holland](/Parts_of_Holland) existed in Lincolnshire, England, until its dissolution in 1974. The focus here, however, remains resolutely on the Dutch territories.

